@node a_cosa_serve "About MiraNAVIGATOR V.1.0"

        MiraNAVIGATOR is helpful for 'navigate'  through a 
        device that contains al lot of Lha archive and the
        respective Rea file in the format:
                    XXXXXXX.Lha
                    XXXXXXX.Rea
                    YYYYYYY.Lha
                    YYYYYYY.Rdm
        If you indicate a device, MiraNAVIGATOR  scans all 
        the directory  and the sub-directory  at the quest
        of XXXXXXXX.Lha files.
        When an  XXXXXXXX.Lha file  is find,  the  program
        search  for  XXXXXXXX.(Rea|Rdm|Readme) and  if  it
        find  a comment  file relative  to XXXXXXXX.Lha it
        read the contens and return  the short description
        concerning XXXXXXXX.Lha file.
        The  results  was  show  by the help of  MultiView
        because  the file  contains  all the  list of  the
        device is in AmigaGuide format.

@endnode
@node come_funziona "Usage of MiraNAVIGATOR V.1.0"

        In the gadget "Device" the  user must indicate the
        device that he want to make the guide file.
        The name of the device must terminate with the ":"
        if you  want to make the  guide of a directory you
        must make an assign and then specify it as device.
        Is better  use the name of  the volume  instead of
        the name of the device:

              Ex.   Use "EARSANCD:" instead of "CD0:"
                    Use "Lavoro:" instead of "DH1:"

        In the gadget  "File" the user  must indicate  the
        name of the AmigaGuide file to create for navigate
        through the device.
        If a lot of fast memory  is available I suggest to
        create  the  AmigaGuide file  in "Ram:"  for  make
        faster the frequently acces to this file.
        
        In the gadget "Ext Pat" is indicated  the complete
        path  (ending with "/" or ":")  where do  you want
        the files were uncompressed when selected.
        When all  the  parameters  are specify  press  the
        gadget start for begin the operations.
        --------------------------------------------------
        You  may call  MiraFIND directly in  MiraNAVIGATOR
        with the gadget "MiraFIND".
        --------------------------------------------------

@endnode
@node installazione "Request & Installation"

        For work correctly MiraNAVIGATOR needs:

          1 - The "List" command in OS 3.0/3.1 version.

          2 - "XHelvetica/13" must be present in
              your "FONTS:" device.

@endnode
